 boy and she would never, never abuse him any more! But he would lie there cold 
and white and make no sign -- a poor little sufferer, whose griefs were at an en
d. He so worked upon his feelings with the pathos of these dreams, that he had t
o keep swallowing, he was so like to choke; and his eyes swam in a blur of water
, which overflowed when he winked, and ran down and trickled from the end of his
 nose. And such a luxury to him was this petting of his sorrows, that he could n
ot bear to have any worldly cheeriness or any grating delight intrude upon it; i
t was too sacred for such contact; and so, presently, when his cousin Mary dance
