 dry argument was resumed. Presently he bethought-63-him of a treasure he had an
d got it out. It was a large black beetle with formidable jaws -- a "pinchbug," 
he called it. It was in a percussion-cap box. The first thing the beetle did was
 to take him by the finger. A natural fillip followed, the beetle went flounderi
ng into the aisle and lit on its back, and the hurt finger went into the boy's m
