in't fair; you just let him alone.""Blame it, I ain't going to stir him much.""L
et him alone, I tell you.""I won't!""You shall -- he's on my side of the line.""
Look here, Joe Harper, whose is that tick?"" I don't care whose tick he is -- he
's on my side of the line, and you sha'n't touch him.""Well, I'll just bet I wil
