hat a superstition of his had failed, here, which he and all his comrades had al
ways looked upon as infallible. If you buried a marble with certain necessary in
cantations, and left it alone a fortnight, and then opened the place with the in
cantation he had just used, you would find that all the marbles you had ever los
t had gathered themselves together there, meantime, no matter how widely they ha
