 himself for great occasions by getting pretty well fuddled, and the sign-painte
r's boy said that when the dominie had reached the proper condition on Examinati
on Evening he would "manage the thing" while he napped in his chair; then he wou
ld have him awakened at the right time and hurried away to school.In the fulness
 of time the interesting occasion arrived. At eight in the evening the schoolhou
se was brilliantly lighted, and adorned with wreaths and festoons of foliage and
 flowers. The master sat throned in his great chair upon a raised platform, with
 his blackboard behind him. He was looking tolerably mellow. Three rows of bench
