XXIVTOM was a glittering hero once more -- the pet of the old, the envy of the y
oung. His name even went into immortal print, for the village paper magnified hi
m. There were some that believed he would be President, yet, if he escaped hangi
ng.As usual, the fickle, unreasoning world took Muff Potter to its bosom and fon
