al. 'Come, there's half my plan done now! How puzzling all these changes are! I'
m never sure what I'm going to be, from one minute to another! However, I've got
 back to my right size: the next thing is, to get into that beautiful gardenhow
 IS that to be done, I wonder?' As she said this, she came suddenly upon an open
 place, with a little house in it about four feet high. 'Whoever lives there,' t
hought Alice, 'it'll never do to come upon them THIS size: why, I should frighte
n them out of their wits!' So she began nibbling at the righthand bit again, and
 did not venture to go near the house till she had brought herself down to nine 
inches high.CHAPTER VI. Pig and PepperFor a minute or two she stood looking at t
he house, and wondering what to do next, when suddenly a footman in livery came 
