ndeed,' said Alice.'Come, let's try the first figure!' said the Mock Turtle to t
he Gryphon. 'We can do without lobsters, you know. Which shall sing?''Oh, YOU si
ng,' said the Gryphon. 'I've forgotten the words.'So they began solemnly dancing
 round and round Alice, every now and then treading on her toes when they passed
 too close, and waving their forepaws to mark the time, while the Mock Turtle sa
